1. a) Find out what networking devices are installed in the department.
   b) Describe the network type and topology.
   c) File and printer sharing in different OS.
   d) Network address config in different OS.
   e) Find IP & MAC id in different OS.
   f) User group and domain config.
   g) Use of utilities: arp, ipconfig/ifconfig/ tracert, nslookup.

2. Examine packet flow across a network segment and see the operation of various Internet protocols across the different layers in the TCP/IP stack. 
(Hint: Use utilities netstat, snoop, tcpdump, ...)

3. a) Use Unix sockets to implement a simple client and server that communicate over the network. 
   b) Write a program to implement daytime server that responds with the day and time to the request sent by client.

   